---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="How I Help - Fix the Chaos">
	<main class="mx-auto w-full text-black text-xl leading-relaxed">

		<!-- Hero Section -->
		<section class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-blue-800 py-20 w-full">
			<div class="container mx-auto px-6 max-w-5xl text-center">
				<h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-white mb-6">You built a business. Now it's breaking you.</h1>
				<p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-blue-100 mb-8 max-w-4xl mx-auto">I help small teams scale without chaos—by fixing the operations spine and using AI the right way.</p>
				<a href="/contact" class="inline-block bg-white text-blue-600 font-semibold py-4 px-8 rounded-lg text-lg hover:bg-blue-50 transition duration-300">Let's start with an audit</a>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Section 1: The Hidden Cost of Success -->
		<section class="py-16 px-6">
			<div class="container mx-auto max-w-4xl">
				<h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-8 text-center">The Hidden Cost of Success</h2>
				<div class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-6">
					<p>From the outside, everything looks fine.<br>
					You've got clients, a small team, solid revenue.<br>
					But inside?</p>
					
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4">
						<li>No onboarding.</li>
						<li>SOPs that live in your head.</li>
						<li>You're still the one answering questions, putting out fires, and fixing the same issues again and again.</li>
					</ul>
					
					<p>Every decision runs through you.<br>
					You can't unplug without something falling apart.</p>
					
					<p class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-600 text-center mt-8">This is the cost of a business that grew without the structure to support it.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Section 2: Why Most Fixes Don't Work -->
		<section class="py-16 px-6 bg-gray-50">
			<div class="container mx-auto max-w-4xl">
				<h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-8 text-center">Why Most Fixes Don't Work</h2>
				<div class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-6">
					<p>You've tried the usual playbook:</p>
					
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4">
						<li>More tools</li>
						<li>More hires</li>
						<li>"Just delegate it"</li>
					</ul>
					
					<p>But the chaos doesn't stop. Because delegation without documentation is just abdication.<br>
					And AI? It's just giving a robot access to your mess.</p>
					
					<div class="text-center mt-8">
						<p class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800">You don't need more stuff.</p>
						<p class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-600">You need a spine—a core system that holds everything up.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Section 3: What Actually Works -->
		<section class="py-16 px-6">
			<div class="container mx-auto max-w-4xl">
				<h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-8 text-center">What Actually Works</h2>
				<div class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-6">
					<p>After auditing business after business, I started seeing the same patterns:</p>
					
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4">
						<li>The founder was the bottleneck</li>
						<li>Everyone was busy but misaligned</li>
						<li>No feedback loops, no operating rhythm</li>
					</ul>
					
					<p>So I shifted. I stopped doing audits that sat in a drawer.<br>
					And started helping founders embed operational clarity.</p>
					
					<p>Sometimes we started with onboarding.<br>
					Sometimes internal comms.<br>
					Sometimes it was just fixing how a task moved from idea to done.</p>
					
					<p>But the outcome was the same:</p>
					
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4">
						<li>Fewer bottlenecks</li>
						<li>Smarter decisions</li>
						<li>Teams that move without micromanagement</li>
						<li>AI that actually works</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Section 4: What I See Most Often -->
		<section class="py-16 px-6 bg-gray-50">
			<div class="container mx-auto max-w-6xl">
				<h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-12 text-center">What I See Most Often</h2>
				
				<div class="overflow-x-auto">
					<table class="w-full bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg">
						<thead class="bg-blue-600 text-white">
							<tr>
								<th class="px-6 py-4 text-left font-semibold">Bottleneck</th>
								<th class="px-6 py-4 text-left font-semibold">Breakdown</th>
								<th class="px-6 py-4 text-left font-semibold">Burnout</th>
							</tr>
						</thead>
						<tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
							<tr>
								<td class="px-6 py-4">
									<div class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Owner-as-Glue</div>
									
								</td>
								<td class="px-6 py-4">
									<div class="text-gray-600">Every decision flows through one person</div>
									
								</td>
								<td class="px-6 py-4">
									<div class="text-gray-600">Team feels stuck. You feel fried</div>
									
								</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
                <tr>
								<td class="px-6 py-4">
									<div class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Frankenstein Stack</div>
									
								</td>
								<td class="px-6 py-4">
									<div class="text-gray-600">10 tools doing 3 jobs badly</div>
									
								</td>
								<td class="px-6 py-4">
									<div class="text-gray-600">Confusion, duplication, wasted time</div>
									
								</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td class="px-6 py-4">
									<div class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Ghost SOPs</div>
									
								</td>
								<td class="px-6 py-4">
									<div class="text-gray-600">Docs no one uses or trusts</div>
								</td>
								<td class="px-6 py-4">
									<div class=" text-gray-600">Tribal knowledge reigns</div>
								</td>
							</tr>

              <tr>
								<td class="px-6 py-4">
									<div class="font-semibold text-gray-800">Delegation Traps</div>
									
								</td>
								<td class="px-6 py-4">
									<div class="text-gray-600">Handoff = hand grenade</div>
									
								</td>
								<td class="px-6 py-4">
									<div class="text-gray-600">Owner still redoes the work</div>
									
								</td>
							</tr>
						</tbody>
					</table>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Section 5: My Core Belief -->
		<section class="py-16 px-6 bg-blue-600 text-white">
			<div class="container mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center">
				<h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8">My Core Belief</h2>
				<h3 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold mb-6">AI Doesn't Fix Chaos. It Accelerates It.</h3>
				
				<div class="text-lg leading-relaxed space-y-6">
					<p>If your business runs on memory, chaos, and hope, AI will just get you to burnout faster.</p>
					
					<p>But if you build a foundation of systems, structure, and clarity?<br>
					AI becomes your second brain.<br>
					You finally get to lead instead of react.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Section 6: How I Can Help You -->
		<section class="py-16 px-6">
			<div class="container mx-auto max-w-4xl">
				<h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-8 text-center">How I Can Help You</h2>
				
				<div class="text-center mb-8">
					<h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-600 mb-4">Let's Break the Cycle</h3>
				</div>
				
				<div class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-6">
					<p>I work with small business owners (5 to 15 people, ~$1M in revenue) who are stuck in the chaos of success.</p>
					
					<p>We codify what works.<br>
					Fix what's fragile.<br>
					And layer in AI only when the business is ready for it.</p>
					
					<p class="text-xl font-semibold text-center text-gray-800">No plug-and-play product. No band-aid fixes. Just deep clarity and operational sanity.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="text-center mt-12">
					<a href="/contact" class="inline-block bg-blue-600 text-white font-semibold py-4 px-8 rounded-lg text-lg hover:bg-blue-700 transition duration-300">Start with an audit</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

	</main>
</Layout>
